1. The actual process is: you have to get into both simultaneously. But generally, discussion sections are harder to get into because they are smaller / are less likely to have open seats, yes.

2. No.

3. By "enrolling afterwards" or "switching", do you mean, dropping the course and rewaitlisting under a different section? If so, how advantageous this would be would really depend the enrollment state of the respective sections at that time.
